==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maturate
<hw>Mat"u*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Maturated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Maturating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>maturatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>maturare</ets> to make ripe, fr.
<ets>maturus</ets> ripe, mature. See <er>Mature</er>, <pos>v.</pos> &
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To bring to ripeness or maturity;
to ripen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A tree may be <qex>maturated</qex> artificially.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To promote the perfect suppuration of (an
abscess).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maturate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Maturate
<hw>Mat"u*rate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To ripen; to become mature;
specifically, to suppurate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maturation</ent>⟦br⟧
